00:15:30,370 --> 00:15:31,780
with you behind bars.

270
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:36,030
I'm shaking in my custom baby seal leather boots.

271
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:38,130
You will leave Metrocity,

272
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:39,510
or this will be the last.

273
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:42,560
You ever hear of Roxanne Ritchi.

274
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:46,170
Roxanne! Don't panic,Roxie.

275
00:15:46,390 --> 00:15:48,180
- I'm on my way. - Yeah,I'm not panicking.

276
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:51,240
In order to stop me,you need to find me first,

277
00:15:51,490 --> 00:15:52,550
Metro man.

278
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:53,970
We're at the abandoned observatory.

279
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:55,970
No,we're not!

280
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:58,090
Don't listen to her,she's crazy.

281
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,760
Metro man approaching,sir.

282
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:42,600
Hold on a second.

283
00:16:49,860 --> 00:16:51,650
Oh,good heavens!

284
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:55,860
You didn't think you were in the real observatory,did you?

285
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,250
Ready the death ray,minion.

286
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:04,850
Death ray,readying.

287
00:17:09,330 --> 00:17:10,650
Over here,old friend.

288
00:17:10,940 --> 00:17:11,920
In case you haven't noticed,

289
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:14,200
you've fallen right into my trap.

290
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:15,330
You can't trap justice.

291
00:17:15,670 --> 00:17:17,220
It's an idea,a belief.

292
00:17:17,430 --> 00:17:19,160
Even the most heartfelt belief

293
00:17:19,380 --> 00:17:20,690
can be corroded over time.

294
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:22,600
Justice is a non-corrosive metal.

295
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:25,160
But metals can be melted by the heat of revange.

296
00:17:25,370 --> 00:17:27,350
It's "revenge," and it's best served cold.

297
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,970
But it can be easily reheated in the microwave of evil.

298
00:17:30,190 --> 00:17:32,130
Well,I think your warranty is about to expire.

299
00:17:32,310 --> 00:17:33,540
Maybe I got an extended warranty.

300
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:35,040
Warranties are invalid if you don't

301
00:17:35,230 --> 00:17:36,490
use the product for its intended purpose.

302
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,560
Oh,girls,girls,you're both pretty.

303
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,510
can I go home now?

304
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:43,000
Of course. that is,if Metro Man can withstand the full,

305
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,660
concentrated power of the sun!

306
00:17:47,010 --> 00:17:47,660
Fire!

307
00:17:58,090 --> 00:17:59,620
Minion. fire?

308
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:02,190
- It's still warming up,sir. - Come again?

309
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:05,710
- Warming up,sir. - Warming up? the sun is warming up?

310
00:18:05,950 --> 00:18:09,860
One second more and...

311
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:15,070
...just tippy-tappy tippy-tap-tap,tip-top more,

312
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:17,560
- and we are ready in just... - Honestly!

313
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,820
On my way,roxie.

314
00:18:19,020 --> 00:18:22,160
I told you to have things ready. I told you countless times.

315
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,450
Why do you always blame me?

316
00:18:24,290 --> 00:18:25,880
My spider bite is acting up.

317
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:28,520
Your plan is failing. Just admit it.

318
00:18:28,730 --> 00:18:30,010
Yeah,good luck with that one.

319
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:31,820
Whose side are you on?

320
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:33,630
- The losing side. - Thank you.

321
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,920
Could someone stamp my frequent kidnapping card?

322
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:42,740
You of all people know we discontinued that promotion.

323
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:44,800
- Ciao-ciao,all! - Same time next week?

324
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,720
Dag! Crab nuggets!

325
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,840
- What did he just say? - "Crab nuggets"?

326
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:55,140
Fackled fish cracker!

327
00:18:55,630 --> 00:18:57,330
Ten seconds to full power.

328
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,770
- Good lord,I'm trapped. - Ten...

329
00:18:59,980 --> 00:19:01,690
- What kind of trickery is this? - ...nine...

330
00:19:01,910 --> 00:19:03,600
- You mad genius. -...eight...

331
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:06,760
- Your dark gift has finally paid off. -...seven...

332
00:19:06,990 --> 00:19:08,430
- It... it has? -...six...

333
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:12,040
This dome is obviously lined with copper.

334
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:14,750
- Yeah? So? - Sir...

335
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:17,500
- Copper drains my powers. -...two...

336
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,700
- Your weakness is copper? -...one.

337
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:21,930
- You're kidding,right? - Full power.

338
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:50,280
I don't think even he could survive that.

339
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:54,410
Well,let's not get our hopes up just yet.

340
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:57,170
- Look! - Metro man!

341
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:58,790
Metro man.

342
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,300
Metro man!

343
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:19,920
- You... you did it,sir. - I did it?

344
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:24,780
He did it.

345
00:20:25,450 --> 00:20:27,970
- I did it? - He did it.

346
00:20:28,310 --> 00:20:29,830
- You did it,sir. - I did it!

347
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:33,670
- You did it! - I did it! Metrocity is mine!

348
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:38,910
- You did it,sir! - I did it! Yeah,me,me!

349
00:20:39,150 --> 00:20:42,190
- Yes,I did it! - Us! We both did it!

350
00:20:42,430 --> 00:20:43,270
- Not us! I! - You,a little more

351
00:20:43,470 --> 00:20:45,120
- than me but still,come on! - A lot more than you.

352
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:46,730
When they're giving out the awards,

353
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:48,480
I'm gonna be right there next to you.

354
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:49,670
What awards? What awards,for what?

355
00:20:50,370 --> 00:20:50,990
Hit it!

356
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:24,230
Drop 'em!

357
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:54,620
First off,what a turnout.

358
00:21:54,930 --> 00:21:57,050
How wild is this?

359
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:02,700
All I did was eliminate the most powerful man in the universe.

360
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:06,740
Are there any questions? Go on. Yes! you in the back.

361
00:22:06,970 --> 00:22:11,370
I'm sure we'd all like to know what you plan to do with us and this city.

362
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,330
Good,I'm glad you asked that.

363
00:22:13,620 --> 00:22:16,980
Imagine the most horrible,terrifying,

364
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,880
evil thing you can possibly think of,

365
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:24,060
And multiply it... by six!

366
00:22:25,560 --> 00:22:26,580
In the meantime,

367
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:30,680
I want you to carry on with the dreary,normal things

368
00:22:31,270 --> 00:22:33,130
you normal people do.

369
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,220
Let's just have fun with this. Come on.

370
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,700
And I will get back to you.

371
00:22:43,060 --> 00:22:44,720
Now slam the door really hard.

372
00:22:47,210 --> 00:22:48,180
They... they can still see you.

373
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:49,660
- Now? - Your elbow's still in.

374
00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:51,110
Good.

375
00:22:54,710 --> 00:22:59,130
There he is,Mr. evil overlord

376
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:02,870
Oh,Minion,did you think this day would ever come?

377
00:23:03,430 --> 00:23:05,350
No way. Not at all,sir.

378
00:23:05,630 --> 00:23:07,430
Never. never in a million... I mean...

379
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:11,630
- Yes,I did. - Look at the intricate mouldings.

380
00:23:11,850 --> 00:23:13,840
I'm looking. I'm looking.

381
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:14,920
And what's this?

382
00:23:16,220 --> 00:23:19,060
It's like one of the giant monitors in the lair.

383
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:21,650
But it seems to only carry one station.

384
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:24,880
Oh,that,sir,is called a window.

385
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:27,830
- Window? - All the kids are looking through them.

386
00:23:29,690 --> 00:23:31,260
I've never had a view before.

387
00:23:32,170 --> 00:23:34,790
Metrocity,Minion,it's all mine.

388
00:23:36,610 --> 00:23:38,180
If my parents could see me now.

389
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:42,450
Sir,I'm sure they're smiling down from evil heaven.

390
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:46,380
And now that Mr. goody two-shoes is out of the way,

391
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:49,170
I can have everything I want,

392
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:52,020
and there's no one to stop me!

393
00:24:35,090 --> 00:24:37,150
I know. I know.

394
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:41,170
Always thirsty,never satisfied.

395
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:44,730
I understand you,little well-dressed bird.

396
00:24:45,830 --> 00:24:50,360
Purposeless,emptiness. it's a vacuum,isn't it?

397
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:52,920
It's... What's your vacuum like?

398
00:24:58,260 --> 00:24:59,700
Not now,minion.

399
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:04,160
I'm in a heated,existential discussion

400
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:06,990
with this dead-eyed,plastic desk toy.

401
00:25:10,130 --> 00:25:12,480
Is... is something wrong,sir?

402
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:15,450
Just think about it.

403
00:25:16,230 --> 00:25:17,260
We have it all.

404
00:25:18,990 --> 00:25:20,080
Yet,we have nothing.

405
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:23,580
It's just too easy now.

406
00:25:25,150 --> 00:25:26,620
I'm sorry,you've lost me,sir.

407
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:31,430
I mean,we did it,right?

408
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:33,560
Well,you did it,sir.

409
00:25:33,850 --> 00:25:35,930
Yes,you've made that perfectly clear.

410
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:40,630
Then why do I feel so... mel-on-choly.

411
00:25:40,890 --> 00:25:42,030
"Mel-on-choly"?

412
00:25:42,840 --> 00:25:44,380
- Unhappy. - Well...

413
00:25:45,610 --> 00:25:47,640
What if tomorrow,

414
00:25:47,890 --> 00:25:50,410
we could go kidnap Roxanne Ritchi.

415
00:25:50,620 --> 00:25:52,580
That always seems to lift your spirits.

416
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:56,190
Good idea,Minion.

417
00:25:56,490 --> 00:25:59,050
but without him,what's the point?

418
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:02,020
- "Him," sir? - Nothing.

419
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:07,070
Ok,all right. we'll just... that's something to consider...

420
00:26:07,260 --> 00:26:10,930
...and... well,I think I'll just power down for a while then.

421
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:21,910
He was always there for us. Dependable.

422
00:26:24,090 --> 00:26:26,410
Perhaps we took him for granted. You know,maybe,

423
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:29,970
We never really know how good we have it until it's gone.

424
00:26:31,450 --> 00:26:35,040
We miss you,Metro Man. I miss you.

425
00:26:36,210 --> 00:26:38,760
And I have just one question.

426
00:26:39,290 --> 00:26:40,800
Are you happy now?

427
00:26:43,940 --> 00:26:45,250
This is Roxanne Ritchi,

428
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:46,780
reporting from a city without a hero.

429
00:26:48,200 --> 00:26:52,360
Coming up next,are you ready to be a slave army? What you need to know.

430
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:03,230
And... wrap that up and give it to a child on christmas,

431
00:27:03,440 --> 00:27:06,070
- 'Cause we're done. - Ok. See you tomorrow,Hal.

432
00:27:06,340 --> 00:27:09,510
Wait. Roxie,I'm having a party at my house.

433
00:27:09,710 --> 00:27:11,470
It's gonna be,like,off the hook,or whatever.

434
00:27:11,660 --> 00:27:13,000
You should come over. I got a deejay,

435
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,130
Rented a bouncy house,made a gallon of dip.

436
00:27:15,330 --> 00:27:16,250
It's gonna be sick.

437
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:18,220
Oh. I... I don't know,Hal.

438
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:20,370
I don't really feel like being around a bunch of people.

439
00:27:20,590 --> 00:27:22,350
No,no,no,that's the best part. it'll just be like you and me.

440
00:27:24,910 --> 00:27:28,500
Wow. That... that's certainly very tempting,but...

441
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:31,760
I did hire a wedding photographer. that's just in case we were like,

442
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:33,810
something crazy happened and we wanted a picture of it.

443
00:27:34,030 --> 00:27:37,050
Like,maybe we should have this for,like,ever. like a memory,you know?

444
00:27:37,290 --> 00:27:39,010
I'm gonna pass.

445
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:42,030
I have some work here that I need to do,anyway.

446
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:44,520
Cool. So Thursday? Soft Thursday?

447
00:27:44,750 --> 00:27:46,630
- Good night,Hal. - That's a soft yes on Thursday.

448
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:51,950
What's wrong with me? Rented a bouncy house?

449
00:27:52,320 --> 00:27:53,840
Chicks don't like bouncy houses.

450
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:54,930
They like clowns.

451
00:27:57,240 --> 00:27:59,350
Stupid van! You broke my finger!

452
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:38,730
I've made a horrible mistake.

453
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:41,270
I didn't mean to destroy you.

454
00:28:41,650 --> 00:28:44,170
I mean,I meant to destroy you,

455
00:28:44,570 --> 00:28:46,540
But I didn't think it would really work.

456
00:28:47,470 --> 00:28:48,850
What are we supposed to do?

457
00:28:49,610 --> 00:28:53,430
Without you,evil is running rampant through the streets.

458
00:28:53,650 --> 00:28:56,840
I'm so tired of running rampant through the streets.

459
00:28:57,930 --> 00:28:59,010
What's the point of being bad

460
00:28:59,230 --> 00:29:00,980
when there's no good to try and stop you?

461
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,580
Someone has to stop Megamind.

462
00:29:04,790 --> 00:29:06,760
- Hey,we're closing soon. - You scared me.

463
00:29:07,250 --> 00:29:08,820
- Barry,right? - Bernard.

464
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:13,250
Bernard. I was just... well,I was talking to myself.

465
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:14,850
You probably think I'm a little bit nuts.

466
00:29:15,170 --> 00:29:16,910
I'm not allowed to insult guests directly.

467
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:19,840
Thank you. Just... Bernard,I'll just be another minute.

468
00:29:21,990 --> 00:29:22,740
Ok.

469
00:29:22,950 --> 00:29:23,740
Thanks.

470
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:27,120
I had so many evil plans in the works.

471
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:29,230
The illiteracy beam.

472
00:29:29,930 --> 00:29:31,260
Typhoon cheese.

473
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,060
Robo-sheep.

474
00:29:33,860 --> 00:29:37,380
Battles we will now never have.

475
00:29:39,280 --> 00:29:41,580
You know,I never had the chance to say goodbye.

476
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,770
So it's good that we have this time now.

477
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:47,280
You know,before I destroy the place.

478
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:50,830
Nothing personal,it just brings back too many painful memories.

479
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:55,880
Hello?

480
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:57,910
- Hello? - Roxanne.

481
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:10,500
- That's a pretty tasteless costume. - Costume?

482
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:13,380
Megamind's head is not that grossly exaggerated.

483
00:30:15,460 --> 00:30:19,170
And you even made a cheap replica of his dehydration gun. How...

484
00:30:20,780 --> 00:30:22,130
Hello? Is someone there?

485
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:27,090
Hello? Who's there?

486
00:30:30,490 --> 00:30:31,610
It's just you,Bernard.

487
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:34,260
Yes. it's just me. Bernard.

488
00:30:34,770 --> 00:30:36,720
Well,thank you for letting me stay.

489
00:30:36,940 --> 00:30:39,530
Look,I wouldn't stay here for more than two minutes and 37 seconds

490
00:30:39,730 --> 00:30:41,900
If I were you. we're having the walls and ceiling removed.

491
00:30:42,260 --> 00:30:44,430
Wow,that sounds like quite the renovation.

492
00:30:44,660 --> 00:30:47,100
I guess I'll catch a ride down with you then.

493
00:30:54,170 --> 00:30:57,300
I kept thinking he was gonna do one of his last-minute escapes.

494
00:30:58,390 --> 00:31:00,960
Yeah. He was really good at those.

495
00:31:01,540 --> 00:31:03,720
Oh,if only the world had a reset button.

496
00:31:04,610 --> 00:31:06,440
I've looked into the reset button.

497
00:31:07,450 --> 00:31:09,060
The science is impossible.

498
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:10,910
Oh,Bernard...

499
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:15,560
I didn't know you had... feelings. Are you ok?

500
00:31:16,710 --> 00:31:21,200
Metro Man's gone. and now there's no one left to challenge Megamind.

501
00:31:21,410 --> 00:31:23,380
Oh,come on,Bernard.

502
00:31:23,660 --> 00:31:26,560
As long as there's evil,good will rise up against it.

503
00:31:26,780 --> 00:31:27,940
Oh,I wish.

504
00:31:28,140 --> 00:31:30,910
I believe someone is gonna stand up to Megamind.

505
00:31:31,110 --> 00:31:33,360
- You really think so? - Yeah. I mean,it's like they say,

506
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:35,970
"Heroes aren't born,they're made."

507
00:31:38,950 --> 00:31:41,980
Heroes can be made. that's it!

508
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:44,350
All you need are the right ingredients.

509
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:46,790
- Yeah. Bravery. - Yes.

510
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:47,940
- Strength. - Of course.

511
00:31:48,170 --> 00:31:49,950
- Determination. - Imperative!

512
00:31:50,330 --> 00:31:51,730
And a smidgen of DNA.

513
00:31:52,230 --> 00:31:54,340
Oh,with that,anyone can be a hero!

514
00:31:54,570 --> 00:31:55,260
Yeah!

515
00:31:57,170 --> 00:31:58,020
I think we should run!

516
00:31:58,600 --> 00:31:59,310
Bye!

517
00:32:01,220 --> 00:32:03,260
Time to put the past behind us.

518
00:32:04,740 --> 00:32:06,060
Only the future...

519
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:09,340
I'm too close! I'm genuinely scared right now.

520
00:32:10,270 --> 00:32:11,340
I hope no one's seeing this!

521
00:32:12,580 --> 00:32:15,680
Create a hero? Wait,wait,what? Why would you do that?

522
00:32:15,850 --> 00:32:17,620
So I have someone to fight.

523
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:20,320
Minion,I'm a villain without a hero.

524
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:22,350
A yin with no yang.

525
00:32:22,590 --> 00:32:24,570
