785
00:46:05,080 --> 00:46:06,330
I do,yeah. thanks,space stepmom.

786
00:46:06,580 --> 00:46:07,220
Churros all the way around.

787
00:46:07,460 --> 00:46:10,900
On the count of three,unsheathe your churro.

788
00:46:11,150 --> 00:46:12,600
One,two,three!

789
00:46:12,880 --> 00:46:13,900
To titan!

790
00:46:14,460 --> 00:46:17,010
Tomorrow,you will fight megamind,

791
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:19,540
and the city will know your name.

792
00:46:21,470 --> 00:46:23,970
The city's parks restored to their original glory,

793
00:46:24,210 --> 00:46:28,070
The streets the safest they've been,the banks reopened.

794
00:46:28,300 --> 00:46:30,140
Has something happened to megamind?

795
00:46:30,430 --> 00:46:32,930
Has someone tamed this monster?

796
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,850
This is Roxanne Ritchi,

797
00:46:35,120 --> 00:46:38,540
cautiously optimistic,and pleasantly confused.

798
00:46:38,780 --> 00:46:40,930
Well,you seem in a very good mood tonight,sir.

799
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:44,590
Oh,yes. how long is this going to take,Minion?

800
00:46:44,850 --> 00:46:46,090
Just a few alterations,sir,

801
00:46:46,310 --> 00:46:49,210
and I will be done with your most terrifying cape yet!

802
00:46:49,450 --> 00:46:50,680
I'm calling it...

803
00:46:50,930 --> 00:46:55,070
...the black mamba...

804
00:46:55,290 --> 00:46:56,820
Black mamba. perfect.

805
00:46:57,020 --> 00:46:59,670
Gosh,I am running late. I have to go.

806
00:47:00,020 --> 00:47:01,940
What? Where... where are you going,sir?

807
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:04,250
We have our debut battle with titan tomorrow morning.

808
00:47:04,490 --> 00:47:06,500
We haven't even tested your big battle suit yet.

809
00:47:06,730 --> 00:47:08,100
You attend to the details,Minion.

810
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:10,570
I have to... run a quick errand.

811
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:12,440
You don't run errands.

812
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:14,440
- What's going on here? - What?

813
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:16,030
Oh,wait a minute.

814
00:47:17,170 --> 00:47:20,490
Are you wearing Jean Paul Gaultier's pour homme?

815
00:47:20,710 --> 00:47:23,960
It's just my natural musk. Now,where are the car keys?

816
00:47:26,620 --> 00:47:28,570
This is about Ms. Ritchi,isn't it?

817
00:47:28,820 --> 00:47:30,280
You're going on a date with her.

818
00:47:31,250 --> 00:47:34,980
No,my main man. Get out of town.

819
00:47:35,210 --> 00:47:38,490
Oh,this is bad. This is bad. You've fallen in love with her.

820
00:47:38,750 --> 00:47:40,770
You are forgetting your place,Minion.

821
00:47:41,050 --> 00:47:42,300
Now give me the keys.

822
00:47:44,350 --> 00:47:47,190
What happens when Roxanne finds out who you really are?

823
00:47:47,530 --> 00:47:49,240
She will never find out,

824
00:47:49,470 --> 00:47:51,290
that's the point of lying.

825
00:47:53,070 --> 00:47:54,720
Honestly,if I didn't know any better,

826
00:47:54,960 --> 00:47:57,000
I'd think this was your first day of being evil.

827
00:47:57,220 --> 00:47:58,010
No!

828
00:48:00,090 --> 00:48:01,380
This has gone far enough!

829
00:48:02,870 --> 00:48:04,620
Oh,that was really grown-up!

830
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:09,310
Sir,sir,please. it's for your own good.

831
00:48:09,950 --> 00:48:10,870
Oh,what do you know?

832
00:48:11,090 --> 00:48:12,010
I may not know much,

833
00:48:12,190 --> 00:48:16,200
But I know this,the bad guy doesn't get the girl.

834
00:48:16,410 --> 00:48:18,960
Maybe I don't want to be the bad guy anymore.

835
00:48:22,870 --> 00:48:23,760
You heard me!

836
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:26,200
Who are you?

837
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:29,080
- now,give me the keys! - no!

838
00:48:30,340 --> 00:48:32,840
My sole purpose in life is to look after you.

839
00:48:33,070 --> 00:48:34,860
Well,I don't need you to look after me.

840
00:48:35,110 --> 00:48:38,560
What are you s... what are you saying? you don't need me?

841
00:48:38,780 --> 00:48:42,140
Let me make it clear. Code: I don't need you.

842
00:48:42,350 --> 00:48:43,970
You know what? You know what?

843
00:48:47,010 --> 00:48:49,310
Code: I'll just pack my thing and go!

844
00:48:49,550 --> 00:48:52,000
- Code: Fine!  - Code: fine back!

845
00:48:55,650 --> 00:48:58,270
- Well,good luck on your date! - I will!

846
00:48:58,490 --> 00:49:00,920
- That doesn't even make any sense! - I know!

847
00:49:32,930 --> 00:49:35,720
I know I am so close. I can feel it.

848
00:49:38,190 --> 00:49:41,870
Ok,ok. I just have to take a step back.

849
00:49:48,140 --> 00:49:49,130
Wait a minute.

850
00:50:02,130 --> 00:50:03,340
"Titan."

851
00:50:04,430 --> 00:50:08,540
- what's a Titan? - my super-ears are burning.

852
00:50:10,100 --> 00:50:13,180
I usually just hear criminals. You haven't been naughty,have you?

853
00:50:14,190 --> 00:50:16,240
I'm totally messing with you. I'm totally messing with you.

854
00:50:16,650 --> 00:50:19,290
- The name's Titan. - Titan.

855
00:50:19,530 --> 00:50:21,810
Your very own heroic guardian of pure awesome.

856
00:50:22,120 --> 00:50:23,010
What's your name? Just kidding.

857
00:50:23,250 --> 00:50:24,140
I know everything about you.

858
00:50:25,760 --> 00:50:27,120
And I... and I brought some flowers.

859
00:50:27,370 --> 00:50:30,710
Didn't know what you liked,so I just grabbed,you know,all of them.

860
00:50:32,650 --> 00:50:35,290
Ok,you don't like flowers? Ok,forget the flowers.

861
00:50:35,530 --> 00:50:36,280
What do you want?

862
00:50:36,520 --> 00:50:38,700
Thought maybe we could go for a little flight around town.

863
00:50:38,960 --> 00:50:39,890
Get to know each other first.

864
00:50:41,760 --> 00:50:43,230
This must be very thrilling for you.

865
00:50:43,470 --> 00:50:44,510
What do you think you're doing?!

866
00:50:44,730 --> 00:50:46,850
Oh,am I moving too fast? you're probably right.

867
00:50:47,100 --> 00:50:49,910
I should just rescue you a few times before we get all romantic.

868
00:50:51,800 --> 00:50:52,510
Saved ya.

869
00:50:52,890 --> 00:50:55,110
You are lucky to have such a great hero here.

870
00:50:55,370 --> 00:50:57,840
- Don't you ever... - Oh,no! Somebody do something!

871
00:50:58,140 --> 00:51:00,910
Oh,right,right,duh. I gotcha. I gotcha.

872
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:08,520
That was a close one. You almost died,

873
00:51:08,850 --> 00:51:10,440
- But I saved you. - Building!

874
00:51:15,870 --> 00:51:19,200
Gotcha! I'm sorry. What were you saying?

875
00:51:19,540 --> 00:51:21,600
I couldn't hear you over the sound of me saving your life.

876
00:51:21,830 --> 00:51:23,210
Put me down! right now!

877
00:51:23,420 --> 00:51:25,670
Ok,all right,all right,hold on.

878
00:51:28,690 --> 00:51:29,760
Are you crazy?

879
00:51:30,010 --> 00:51:32,770
I suppose I'm a,I'm a little crazy,about you.

880
00:51:33,210 --> 00:51:35,480
Who are you,really?

881
00:51:35,760 --> 00:51:40,020
Oh,right. Well,prepare to have your mind blown,little lady.

882
00:51:41,590 --> 00:51:43,280
- Ta-da. - Hal?

883
00:51:43,550 --> 00:51:45,850
Yeah. Isn't this great?

884
00:51:46,130 --> 00:51:47,970
Now there's nothing keeping us apart.

885
00:51:48,220 --> 00:51:51,280
- No,it's not great. - Wow,our first fight.

886
00:51:51,560 --> 00:51:52,850
This is so us.

887
00:51:53,090 --> 00:51:54,330
We're like an old married couple.

888
00:51:54,570 --> 00:51:55,760
Look,there is no "us," ok?

889
00:51:55,990 --> 00:51:57,570
There will never be an "us."

890
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:00,050
But... I have powers.

891
00:52:00,730 --> 00:52:02,450
I have a cape. I'm the good guy.

892
00:52:02,710 --> 00:52:05,160
You are a good guy,Hal,but you don't understand.

893
00:52:05,410 --> 00:52:07,260
- We need to find out why... - No,no. this...

894
00:52:07,530 --> 00:52:08,500
- Hal,just take a deep breath - This isn't right!

895
00:52:08,750 --> 00:52:10,810
- And listen to me for a moment. - You're supposed to be with me!

896
00:52:11,070 --> 00:52:13,060
I'm trying to warn you,Hal.

897
00:52:13,300 --> 00:52:17,020
It's Titan! It's Titan,not Hal!

898
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:41,100
- Bernard. - Roxanne.

899
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:42,920
Sorry I'm late.

900
00:52:43,120 --> 00:52:45,770
Wow,your hair looks exciting.

901
00:52:45,980 --> 00:52:48,960
Not the only exciting development of the night.

902
00:52:49,560 --> 00:52:51,210
Megamind's created a new hero,

903
00:52:51,620 --> 00:52:52,760
and I know why.

904
00:52:54,220 --> 00:52:57,150
It all makes sense now. He missed getting his butt kicked,

905
00:52:57,420 --> 00:52:58,520
So he created a new hero

906
00:52:58,750 --> 00:53:00,120
- to kick it for him. - Yeah.

907
00:53:00,460 --> 00:53:02,710
But why would he pick Hal?

908
00:53:03,110 --> 00:53:05,740
Hal is the worst possible person you could pick.

909
00:53:05,970 --> 00:53:07,980
Wow. That's a lot to take in.

910
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:10,090
It boggles my mind.

911
00:53:10,390 --> 00:53:13,490
I am extremely boggled. You know,I'm sure we'll get

912
00:53:13,750 --> 00:53:15,580
To the bottom of who's kicking whose butt.

913
00:53:15,780 --> 00:53:19,590
But in the meantime,let's enjoy each other's company.

914
00:53:20,610 --> 00:53:22,940
I'm sorry,Bernard,of course,you're right.

915
00:53:23,190 --> 00:53:24,550
You know,I could use a breather.

916
00:53:26,050 --> 00:53:27,030
To Bernard,

917
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:31,700
for being the only normal thing in my crazy,upside-down world.

918
00:53:32,350 --> 00:53:35,630
To... being normal.

919
00:53:45,460 --> 00:53:47,000
- Roxanne? - Yes?

920
00:53:48,980 --> 00:53:50,600
Say I wasn't so normal.

921
00:53:51,380 --> 00:53:55,290
Let's say I was bald and had the complexion of,

922
00:53:55,550 --> 00:54:00,040
Of a popular primary color,as a random,nonspecific example.

923
00:54:01,140 --> 00:54:04,030
- Would you still enjoy my company? - Of course!

924
00:54:04,280 --> 00:54:05,700
You don't judge a book by its cover

925
00:54:05,950 --> 00:54:07,400
or a person from the outside.

926
00:54:08,150 --> 00:54:09,330
That's a relief to hear.

927
00:54:09,590 --> 00:54:11,360
You judge them based on their actions.

928
00:54:12,580 --> 00:54:14,430
Well,that seems kind of petty,don't you think?

929
00:54:44,610 --> 00:54:45,600
What? What?

930
00:54:47,660 --> 00:54:50,440
Don't look at me! Just a technical glitch!

931
00:54:51,090 --> 00:54:53,350
Don't look yet! Well,never mind that.

932
00:54:54,960 --> 00:54:55,690
Ok.

933
00:54:57,420 --> 00:54:58,410
Where were we?

934
00:55:01,320 --> 00:55:02,840
- You... - Now,now,hold on.

935
00:55:03,070 --> 00:55:03,960
You!

936
00:55:25,500 --> 00:55:26,560
I can explain!

937
00:55:28,450 --> 00:55:30,190
What about everything you just said?

938
00:55:30,550 --> 00:55:32,560
About judging a book by its cover?

939
00:55:32,800 --> 00:55:35,770
Well,let's take a look at the contents then,shall we?

940
00:55:35,990 --> 00:55:39,100
You destroyed Metroman,you took over the city,

941
00:55:39,330 --> 00:55:43,000
And then,you actually got me to care about you!

942
00:55:44,080 --> 00:55:47,840
Why are you so evil? Tricking me?

943
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:51,150
What could you possibly hope to gain?

944
00:55:56,360 --> 00:56:00,000
Wait a minute. I don't believe this.

945
00:56:03,460 --> 00:56:06,760
Do you really think that I would ever be with you?

946
00:56:09,580 --> 00:56:10,560
No.

947
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:46,590
Ok,Minion! You were right!

948
00:56:46,870 --> 00:56:49,630
I was... less right!

949
00:56:50,060 --> 00:56:53,590
We should stick to what we're good at... being bad.

950
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:56,040
Minion?

951
00:57:15,350 --> 00:57:16,290
You there!

952
00:57:17,650 --> 00:57:18,760
Yeah,you.

953
00:57:19,720 --> 00:57:22,570
Bring out the black mamba.

954
00:57:54,830 --> 00:57:58,990
Ok,Titan. it's time to go down in style.

955
00:58:21,860 --> 00:58:26,370
I hear there's a new hero who dares challenge my evil.

956
00:58:26,830 --> 00:58:29,630
Where is the one they call Titan?

957
00:58:33,450 --> 00:58:36,050
CHallenge me if you dare!

958
00:58:59,010 --> 00:59:00,570
Oh no. We're gonna crash!

959
00:59:04,200 --> 00:59:06,150
This is embarrassing.

960
00:59:12,930 --> 00:59:16,360
Of all the inconsiderate,bone-headed...

961
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:20,050
...irresponsible,rude...

962
00:59:20,470 --> 00:59:22,820
Unprofessional,that's what this is!

963
00:59:23,990 --> 00:59:25,830
Would Metro man have kept me waiting?

964
00:59:26,350 --> 00:59:28,390
Of course not! he was a pro!

965
00:59:28,700 --> 00:59:31,330
Hey,Megamind! You're actually the guy I want to see.

966
00:59:31,740 --> 00:59:33,050
Also,there's a door here.

967
00:59:33,290 --> 00:59:37,010
Do you have any idea how long I waited for you?

968
00:59:37,250 --> 00:59:38,730
No,no,no,I totally understand what you're saying.

969
00:59:38,960 --> 00:59:40,040
Could you just,just shut up for one second.

970
00:59:40,250 --> 00:59:41,340
I'm trying to beat this level.

971
00:59:41,580 --> 00:59:43,500
Were you even planning on showing up?

972
00:59:44,490 --> 00:59:45,240
What's this?

973
00:59:47,840 --> 00:59:49,810
Where did you get all this stuff?

974
00:59:50,040 --> 00:59:51,680
It doesn't belong to me.

975
00:59:51,910 --> 00:59:53,820
- You stole it? - Pretty cool,right?

976
00:59:54,020 --> 00:59:55,500
No,no,no,no! you're a hero!

977
00:59:55,730 --> 00:59:57,200
Being a hero is for losers!

978
00:59:57,430 --> 01:00:00,320
It's work,work,work,24/7,and for what?

979
01:00:00,770 --> 01:00:02,410
I only took the gig to get the girl,

980
01:00:02,670 --> 01:00:04,980
And it turns out Roxanne doesn't want anything to do with me.

981
01:00:05,740 --> 01:00:08,030
- Roxanne Ritchi? - Yeah! Roxanne Ritchi!

982
01:00:08,260 --> 01:00:10,570
I saw her having dinner and making googly eyes

983
01:00:10,810 --> 01:00:12,620
At some intellectual dweeb!

984
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:14,620
Who needs all that noise?

985
01:00:15,100 --> 01:00:18,180
That's why I think we should team up.

986
01:00:18,680 --> 01:00:19,870
You... wait... what?

987
01:00:20,090 --> 01:00:22,120
With my power,and your big-headedness,

988
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:25,650
- We could rule the city! - You want to team up?

989
01:00:25,870 --> 01:00:27,320
I even drew up some new costume designs,see?

990
01:00:27,550 --> 01:00:28,870
- Costume designs? - You'd be the brains,

991
01:00:29,100 --> 01:00:30,200
So you'd get a little brain,

992
01:00:30,390 --> 01:00:31,920
Wearing glasses on your costume,or something.

993
01:00:32,140 --> 01:00:34,110
And since I'm the cool one,I'd have,like,

994
01:00:34,450 --> 01:00:36,320
Two tanks swordfighting...

995
01:00:37,270 --> 01:00:38,450
I can't believe you.

996
01:00:39,090 --> 01:00:41,900
All your gifts,all your powers,

997
01:00:42,120 --> 01:00:45,590
And you... you squander them for your own personal gain.

998
01:00:45,830 --> 01:00:48,460
- Yes! - No! I'm the villain!

999
01:00:48,750 --> 01:00:50,800
You're the good guy! I do something bad,

1000
01:00:51,070 --> 01:00:54,640
And you come and get me! That's why I created you.

1001
01:00:54,860 --> 01:00:58,490
Yeah,right. you're nuts. space dad told me...

1002
01:00:58,710 --> 01:01:00,760
Look,I'm your space dad!

1003
01:01:02,340 --> 01:01:04,320
You should be more like Metro man.

1004
01:01:05,830 --> 01:01:08,560
-You tricked me? - Oh,don't like that?

1005
01:01:08,780 --> 01:01:09,720
Well,there's more.

1006
01:01:11,550 --> 01:01:15,100
I'm also the intellectual dweeb dating Roxanne.

1007
01:01:15,600 --> 01:01:19,200
- No. - And we were smooching up a storm!

1008
01:01:22,190 --> 01:01:23,700
When I get my hands on you,I'm gonna...

1009
01:01:23,720 --> 01:01:26,700
Yes! Yes,I know! Bring me to justice.

1010
01:01:27,100 --> 01:01:29,460
Oh god,how I've missed this.

1011
01:01:32,730 --> 01:01:34,890
And the hero strikes the first blow.

1012
01:01:35,160 --> 01:01:37,050
But evil returns with a backhand!

1013
01:01:42,100 --> 01:01:42,930
Yes!

1014
01:01:51,970 --> 01:01:53,570
Come out,you little freak!

1015
01:01:54,070 --> 01:01:56,920
I want to see what that big brain looks like on the pavement!

1016
01:02:03,890 --> 01:02:06,660
You fell for the oldest evil trick in the book!

1017
01:02:07,630 --> 01:02:09,300
You little blue twerp!

1018
01:02:11,730 --> 01:02:12,650
En garde!

1019
01:02:18,040 --> 01:02:20,210
Oh,now that's the spirit!

1020
01:02:20,510 --> 01:02:22,690
Parry! Thrust! Parry again!

1021
01:02:23,160 --> 01:02:25,940
Now it's time for some witty back and forth banter!

1022
01:02:26,310 --> 01:02:27,480
You go first!

1023
01:02:28,450 --> 01:02:30,950
Ok! look,I'm not sure where to go with that!

1024
01:02:32,700 --> 01:02:34,460
This one's for stealing my girlfriend!

1025
01:02:40,480 --> 01:02:42,820
This one's for space dad making a fool out of me!

1026
01:02:50,720 --> 01:02:55,160
And,Megamind,this one's for space stepmom! you lied to her!

1027
01:02:55,860 --> 01:02:59,260
Well done. I thought that battle went really,really well.

1028
01:02:59,640 --> 01:03:01,870
- I mean,I have a few notes. - Notes?

1029
01:03:02,110 --> 01:03:02,970
But they can wait.

1030
01:03:03,210 --> 01:03:04,160
You can take me to jail now.

1031
01:03:04,390 --> 01:03:08,050
Oh,no,no,no. I was thinking more like the morgue. You're dead!

1032
01:03:08,290 --> 01:03:10,500
Whoa,whoa,whoa,whoa,whoa. This isn't how you play the game.

1033
01:03:10,760 --> 01:03:11,630
Game over.

1034
01:03:18,840 --> 01:03:19,610
Brain-bots!

1035
01:03:25,790 --> 01:03:26,870
I'm calling time out!

1036
01:03:28,060 --> 01:03:30,280
Time out? time out! time out!

1037
01:03:40,900 --> 01:03:43,280
Brain-bots,initiate the fail-safe.

1038
01:03:50,580 --> 01:03:54,490
Guess what,Buster Brown? it's made from copper.

1039
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:56,470
You're powerless against it.

1040
01:03:56,710 --> 01:04:00,640
It's the very same metal used to defeat... Metro man?

1041
01:04:01,350 --> 01:04:04,770
You should stop comparing me to Metro man!

1042
01:04:14,180 --> 01:04:16,580
You can run,Megamind,but you can't hide!

1043
01:04:16,870 --> 01:04:18,570
We're saved! we're saved!

1044
01:04:19,090 --> 01:04:20,660
What's your name,new hero?

1045
01:04:20,910 --> 01:04:22,570
- It's Titan. - Thank you!

1046
01:04:23,080 --> 01:04:25,550
Thank you! Titan has freed us!

1047
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:27,450
Oh,I wouldn't say "free."

1048
01:04:27,720 --> 01:04:30,470
More like under new management.

1049
01:04:36,160 --> 01:04:38,280
- What do you want? - Titan's turned evil.

1050
01:04:38,500 --> 01:04:39,170
Congratulations.

1051
01:04:39,190 --> 01:04:41,150
Another one of your genius plans has backfired on you.

1052
01:04:41,700 --> 01:04:43,600
And why did my doorman let you up?

1053
01:04:45,010 --> 01:04:45,840
Carlos.

1054
01:04:46,560 --> 01:04:48,030
Please,Roxanne,no. no.

1055
01:04:48,580 --> 01:04:49,500
I need your help.

1056
01:04:49,750 --> 01:04:51,640
Why do you need my help?

1057
01:04:53,460 --> 01:04:55,640
Because you're the smartest person I know.

1058
01:04:57,750 --> 01:04:58,730
But you can't hide here.

1059
01:04:58,960 --> 01:04:59,660
The copper should have worked.

1060
01:04:59,890 --> 01:05:01,060
Why didn't the copper work?

1061
01:05:01,280 --> 01:05:02,790
The copper worked perfectly well last time.

1062
01:05:03,000 --> 01:05:04,790
Copper? you're not making any sense.

1063
01:05:05,020 --> 01:05:06,850
Look,if we don't find Titan's weakness,

1064
01:05:07,100 --> 01:05:08,510
He'll destroy the whole city.

1065
01:05:11,310 --> 01:05:12,800
Ok,how can I help?

1066
01:05:13,020 --> 01:05:14,130
We need to find answers.

1067
01:05:14,360 --> 01:05:15,940
You knew Metro man best.

1068
01:05:16,130 --> 01:05:17,890
Did he have a hideout? A cave?

1069
01:05:18,120 --> 01:05:22,310
A solitary fortress of some kind? Anything that would give us clues.

1070
01:05:22,750 --> 01:05:25,230
Well... there is one place I know.

1071
01:05:28,040 --> 01:05:30,620
You gave him these powers. can't you just take them away?

1072
01:05:30,860 --> 01:05:33,470
I can't. I lost my diffuser gun

1073
01:05:33,680 --> 01:05:35,400
when I misplaced the invisible car.

1074
01:05:36,050 --> 01:05:37,000
The night you dumped me,

1075
01:05:37,980 --> 01:05:40,260
alone,in the rain.

1076
01:05:41,740 --> 01:05:42,980
Did you ever look back?

1077
01:05:43,190 --> 01:05:46,350
- No! - My giant blue head!

1078
01:05:46,590 --> 01:05:47,620
I guess we're here.

1079
01:05:50,560 --> 01:05:53,530
So,this is where he hid it.

1080
01:05:53,780 --> 01:05:58,210
After all these years. My old shoolhouse.

1081
01:06:00,510 --> 01:06:03,610
You know,I think there's an apology in order for the other night.

1082
01:06:03,850 --> 01:06:05,730
Ok,that would be nice,but make it quick.

1083
01:06:05,960 --> 01:06:07,880
We have much more pressing matters to deal with.

1084
01:06:11,910 --> 01:06:16,270
Wow. I can't believe he kept all this stuff.

1085
01:06:17,200 --> 01:06:19,510
I remember when he wore that.

1086
01:06:19,740 --> 01:06:20,850
Shouldn't we try to stay focused here?

1087
01:06:21,090 --> 01:06:23,000
Yes,of course,right,focused.

1088
01:06:24,430 --> 01:06:26,020
Hey,come over and look at this.

1089
01:06:26,670 --> 01:06:28,240
What is it? What did you find?

1090
01:06:31,810 --> 01:06:32,690
Look.

1091
01:06:33,190 --> 01:06:35,600
This glass has ice cubes in it.

1092
01:06:35,810 --> 01:06:37,890
Yes,that's what happens when water gets cold.

1093
01:06:38,120 --> 01:06:41,510
No,what I'm saying is,don't you think it's a little odd

1094
01:06:41,730 --> 01:06:43,840
That the ice hasn't melted yet?

1095
01:06:44,050 --> 01:06:45,530
One of life's great mysteries.

1096
01:07:05,310 --> 01:07:06,900
We now have confirmed reports.

1097
01:07:07,220 --> 01:07:09,460
Titan,first thought to be this city's new hero,

1098
01:07:09,710 --> 01:07:10,800
has turned evil.

1099
01:07:11,030 --> 01:07:13,660
The city has never seen this level of destruction.

1100
01:07:13,900 --> 01:07:16,290
If only Metroman were still alive...

1101
01:07:16,340 --> 01:07:17,800
- You're alive? - You're alive.

1102
01:07:19,060 --> 01:07:20,940
- I'm alive. - but I,we...

1103
01:07:21,190 --> 01:07:23,510
We saw your skeleton! you were dead!

1104
01:07:23,750 --> 01:07:24,810
Are you a ghost?

1105
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:28,920
There had better be an amazing explanation for this.

1106
01:07:29,140 --> 01:07:31,100
Speak,apparition.

1107
01:07:41,170 --> 01:07:43,570
Ok. ok,ok,ok.

1108
01:07:43,910 --> 01:07:45,360
You both deserve the truth.

1109
01:07:45,870 --> 01:07:47,780
It all started back at the observatory.

1110
01:07:48,930 --> 01:07:51,390
Roxanne was kidnapped. I was gonna stop you.

1111
01:07:52,670 --> 01:07:54,370
My head wasn't in the game that day.

1112
01:07:55,210 --> 01:07:57,140
We were kind of going through the motions.

1113
01:07:57,660 --> 01:08:01,120
So... using my super-speed,

1114
01:08:01,400 --> 01:08:02,770
I decided to go clear my head.

1115
01:08:03,110 --> 01:08:04,090
Fire!

1116
01:08:05,090 --> 01:08:06,060
Then I realized,

1117
01:08:06,590 --> 01:08:10,330
We had done this same silly charade our entire lives.

1118
01:08:11,440 --> 01:08:13,680
I tried to get my mind off how I was feeling,

1119
01:08:14,390 --> 01:08:16,120
But I just felt stuck.

1120
01:08:17,400 --> 01:08:20,530
I began to realize,despite all my powers,

1121
01:08:21,480 --> 01:08:24,040
Each and every citizen of Metro have something I didn't,

1122
01:08:24,960 --> 01:08:25,800
a choice.

1123
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:28,620
Ever since I can remember,

1124
01:08:28,840 --> 01:08:31,010
I've always had to be what the city wanted me to be.

1125
01:08:32,200 --> 01:08:33,940
But what about what I wanted to do?

1126
01:08:35,360 --> 01:08:36,500
Then it suddenly hit me.

1127
01:08:38,210 --> 01:08:39,730
I do have a choice.

1128
01:08:41,210 --> 01:08:43,050
I can be whatever I want to be.

1129
01:08:43,730 --> 01:08:46,010
No one said this hero thing had to be a lifetime gig.

1130
01:08:47,010 --> 01:08:48,390
You can't just quit,either.

1131
01:08:49,500 --> 01:08:53,960
That's when I got the brilliant idea... to fake my death.

1132
01:08:54,740 --> 01:08:57,600
Copper drains my powers.

1133
01:08:57,830 --> 01:08:58,990
Your weakness is copper?

1134
01:09:00,240 --> 01:09:04,570
Once your death ray hit,I'd never felt so alive.

1135
01:09:05,480 --> 01:09:07,820
So I borrowed a prop from a nearby nursing school.

1136
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:11,150
Metroman was finally dead.

1137
01:09:11,670 --> 01:09:13,040
And music man was born!

1138
01:09:13,320 --> 01:09:15,150
- Music man? - That way I could keep my logo.

1139
01:09:15,370 --> 01:09:16,300
- 'Cause of wha...? - Come again?

1140
01:09:16,500 --> 01:09:20,150
I was finally free to get in touch with my true power...

1141
01:09:21,300 --> 01:09:21,960
...weaving lyrical magic.

1142
01:09:22,880 --> 01:09:23,810
Check this out.

1143
01:09:24,250 --> 01:09:27,360
I have eyes that can see

1144
01:09:27,630 --> 01:09:31,240
right through lead...

1145
01:09:31,520 --> 01:09:33,640
- You're horrible! - Granted,you have talent.

1146
01:09:33,850 --> 01:09:37,130
But there's a madman out there destroying our... your city.

1147
01:09:37,830 --> 01:09:39,530
How could you do this?!

1148
01:09:40,770 --> 01:09:42,350
The people of this city relied on you,

1149
01:09:42,570 --> 01:09:43,670
and you deserted them!

1150
01:09:44,560 --> 01:09:46,770
You left us in the hands of him!

1151
01:09:47,110 --> 01:09:48,930
- No offense. - No,I'm with you.

1152
01:09:49,500 --> 01:09:51,100
Look,we need your help.

1153
01:09:51,630 --> 01:09:54,180
I'm sorry. I really am.

1154
01:09:55,270 --> 01:09:56,260
I'm done.

1155
01:09:56,970 --> 01:09:58,350
You know,little buddy,

1156
01:09:58,950 --> 01:10:00,450
there's a yin for every yang.

1157
01:10:00,950 --> 01:10:03,940
If there's bad,good will rise up against it.

1158
01:10:04,790 --> 01:10:07,190
It's taken me a long time to find my calling.

1159
01:10:08,440 --> 01:10:10,890
Now it's about time you find yours.

1160
01:10:16,560 --> 01:10:17,810
Hey,who needs him?

1161
01:10:18,360 --> 01:10:20,050
We can beat Titan ourselves.

1162
01:10:20,270 --> 01:10:23,120
I say we go back to the evil lair,grab some ray guns,

1163
01:10:23,360 --> 01:10:25,810
Hold him sideways,and just go all gangsta on him.

1164
01:10:26,800 --> 01:10:27,730
We can't.

1165
01:10:28,180 --> 01:10:30,080
So that's it? you're just giving up?

1166
01:10:30,360 --> 01:10:33,230
I'm the bad guy. I don't save the day,

1167
01:10:33,450 --> 01:10:35,160
I don't fly off into the sunset,

1168
01:10:35,440 --> 01:10:37,430
And I don't get the girl.

1169
01:10:38,430 --> 01:10:39,600
I'm going home.

1170
01:11:09,600 --> 01:11:13,540
Unless someone comes to our aid soon,all may be lost.

1171
01:11:14,790 --> 01:11:17,830
Thousands have already fled the city in a mass exodus.

1172
01:11:18,110 --> 01:11:22,130
Remaining citizens are warned to stay indoors until further notice.

1173
01:11:23,780 --> 01:11:25,380
Authorities have issued a warning

1174
01:11:25,610 --> 01:11:29,020
To stay out of the downtown area at all costs.

1175
01:11:41,000 --> 01:11:42,040
Hal!

1176
01:11:43,450 --> 01:11:44,220
Hal!

1177
01:11:46,190 --> 01:11:48,680
Let me guess. After seeing how awesome I am,

1178
01:11:48,990 --> 01:11:52,220
You've finally come to your senses? well,I'm over you.

1179
01:11:52,460 --> 01:11:55,810
- I've come to stop you,Hal. - You? oh,wow.

1180
01:11:56,030 --> 01:11:57,810
Ok,what are you gonna do,report me to death?

1181
01:11:58,030 --> 01:11:59,680
I was going to try reasoning with you.

1182
01:12:00,130 --> 01:12:02,680
You and I,we worked together for a long time.

1183
01:12:03,100 --> 01:12:04,240
I know you.

1184
01:12:04,470 --> 01:12:07,840
You don't know me. You never took the time to know me.

1185
01:12:08,100 --> 01:12:10,510
This is the first time we've hung out socially,

1186
01:12:10,760 --> 01:12:12,600
And it's when I'm about to destroy the city!

1187
01:12:12,840 --> 01:12:14,210
I want to talk to the real Hal.

1188
01:12:14,560 --> 01:12:17,060
I want to talk to the guy who loved being a cameraman,

1189
01:12:17,280 --> 01:12:19,340
And eating dip,and being a nerd,

1190
01:12:19,570 --> 01:12:21,680
And being not as scary as the Tighten Hal.

1191
01:12:21,900 --> 01:12:23,020
Too late!

1192
01:12:25,240 --> 01:12:26,320
... interrupting our scheduled...

1193
01:12:26,540 --> 01:12:28,000
... extraordinary events taking place...

1194
01:12:28,260 --> 01:12:29,840
Heat in the valley and...

1195
01:12:30,140 --> 01:12:31,130
Megamind!

1196
01:12:33,540 --> 01:12:36,300
You and I have some unfinished business.

1197
01:12:36,530 --> 01:12:38,020
I'll be waiting at metro tower.

1198
01:12:38,240 --> 01:12:40,630
Oh,and just so you don't get cold feet...

1199
01:12:42,550 --> 01:12:43,400
Roxanne.

1200
01:12:43,790 --> 01:12:44,910
Come on,Roxie,

1201
01:12:45,190 --> 01:12:47,530
call for your hero to come rescue you.

1202
01:12:48,910 --> 01:12:52,490
Megamind,I don't even know if you're listening,

1203
01:12:52,730 --> 01:12:53,790
but if you are,

1204
01:12:54,290 --> 01:12:55,940
You can't give up.

1205
01:12:57,690 --> 01:13:01,410
The Megamind I knew would never have run from a fight,

1206
01:13:01,690 --> 01:13:05,090
Even when he knew he had absolutely no chance of winning.

1207
01:13:05,470 --> 01:13:07,420
It was your best quality.

1208
01:13:07,930 --> 01:13:10,920
You need to be that guy right now.

1209
01:13:12,740 --> 01:13:14,080
The city needs you.

1210
01:13:16,770 --> 01:13:17,940
I need you.

1211
01:13:18,750 --> 01:13:19,650
Roxanne.

1212
01:13:19,890 --> 01:13:21,070
You have one hour.

1213
01:13:21,610 --> 01:13:23,720
Don't keep me waiting.

1214
01:13:25,770 --> 01:13:27,210
Warden! warden!

1215
01:13:27,860 --> 01:13:29,560
listen to me! You have to let me go!

1216
01:13:29,790 --> 01:13:31,710
Tighten has to be stopped!

1217
01:13:32,020 --> 01:13:32,950
Sorry,Megamind.

1218
01:13:33,150 --> 01:13:35,290
you still have 88 life sentences to go.

1219
01:13:35,750 --> 01:13:37,980
Plenty of time to reflect on what you've done.

1220
01:13:38,250 --> 01:13:41,660
Did you want to hear me say it? I'll say it.

1221
01:13:41,950 --> 01:13:45,260
Here it is,from the blackest part of my heart.

1222
01:13:47,820 --> 01:13:50,790
I am sorry!

1223
01:13:53,980 --> 01:13:54,960
Not buying it.

1224
01:13:57,650 --> 01:13:58,790
I don't blame you.

1225
01:14:00,510 --> 01:14:02,840
I've terrorized this city countless times.

1226
01:14:03,640 --> 01:14:06,300
Created a hero who's turned out to be a villain.

1227
01:14:07,870 --> 01:14:09,610
I lied to Roxanne,and...

1228
01:14:10,610 --> 01:14:12,180
...my best friend Minion,

1229
01:14:13,680 --> 01:14:15,220
I treated like dirt.

1230
01:14:17,620 --> 01:14:19,450
Please don't make this city...

1231
01:14:21,220 --> 01:14:24,250
...don't make Roxanne pay for my wrongdoings.

1232
01:14:28,510 --> 01:14:29,860
Apology accepted.

1233
01:14:33,000 --> 01:14:36,680
Oh,Minion,you fantastic fish,you.

1234
01:14:37,110 --> 01:14:39,700
What are we waiting for? We'd better get going.

1235
01:14:42,910 --> 01:14:43,840
You got me.

1236
01:14:47,010 --> 01:14:48,060
Good luck,fellas!

1237
01:14:48,290 --> 01:14:49,390
we're gonna die!

1238
01:14:51,180 --> 01:14:51,960
Wait,what?

1239
01:14:52,630 --> 01:14:55,880
Hey,Metro losers. This is Metro tower.

1240
01:14:56,390 --> 01:14:59,430
They say it's supposed to be a symbol of our city's strength.

1241
01:14:59,640 --> 01:15:01,680
But for me,it's a reminder of the day

1242
01:15:01,900 --> 01:15:04,620
This woman ferociously ripped out my heart.

1243
01:15:04,950 --> 01:15:06,970
And I hate reminders!

1244
01:15:20,480 --> 01:15:21,350
Help!

1245
01:15:23,710 --> 01:15:24,930
Please don't do this.

1246
01:15:25,240 --> 01:15:27,570
I know there's still good in you,Hal.

1247
01:15:27,810 --> 01:15:29,220
You're so naive,Roxie.

1248
01:15:29,470 --> 01:15:31,170
You see the good in everybody,

1249
01:15:31,400 --> 01:15:32,550
even when it's not there.

1250
01:15:32,930 --> 01:15:34,490
You're living a fantasy.

1251
01:15:35,080 --> 01:15:38,080
There is no Easter Bunny,there is no Tooth Fairy,

1252
01:15:38,320 --> 01:15:40,050
And there is no queen of England.

1253
01:15:40,990 --> 01:15:43,910
This is the real world,and you need to wake up!

1254
01:15:56,050 --> 01:15:59,260
You dare challenge Megamind?

1255
01:15:59,710 --> 01:16:02,440
This town isn't big enough for two super-villains!

1256
01:16:02,660 --> 01:16:07,560
Oh,you're a villain all right! Just not a super one!

1257
01:16:07,800 --> 01:16:09,400
Yeah? what's the difference?

1258
01:16:13,710 --> 01:16:14,960
Presentation!

1259
01:16:34,830 --> 01:16:37,780
- I knew you'd come back. - Well,that made one of us.

1260
01:17:04,920 --> 01:17:09,270
- What's the plan? - Well,it mostly involves not dying.

1261
01:17:09,530 --> 01:17:10,470
I like that plan.

1262
01:17:28,460 --> 01:17:29,380
Building!

1263
01:17:31,390 --> 01:17:33,030
Go faster! Make this thing go faster!

1264
01:17:34,980 --> 01:17:36,020
I can't control it!

1265
01:17:51,820 --> 01:17:52,660
No.

1266
01:17:56,010 --> 01:17:57,010
Well,that was easy.

1267
01:17:57,680 --> 01:17:59,530
Looks like there's only one loose end now.

1268
01:18:10,770 --> 01:18:13,910
Please,let's have a little respect for public transportation.

1269
01:18:15,170 --> 01:18:16,350
You came back!

1270
01:18:16,810 --> 01:18:18,060
You were right,Roxanne.

1271
01:18:18,470 --> 01:18:19,870
I never should have left.

1272
01:18:20,210 --> 01:18:22,290
I... I thought you were dead.

1273
01:18:22,500 --> 01:18:25,420
My death was... greatly exaggerated.

1274
01:18:25,740 --> 01:18:28,830
So,you're the punk I've heard about.

1275
01:18:42,070 --> 01:18:45,250
I'm sorry. I did the best I could.

1276
01:18:47,410 --> 01:18:48,910
I'm so proud of you.

1277
01:18:53,070 --> 01:18:53,980
Minion?

1278
01:18:55,030 --> 01:18:56,460
Surprise!

1279
01:18:58,190 --> 01:18:59,950
He's the real hero.

1280
01:19:07,090 --> 01:19:08,010
Megamind.

1281
01:19:10,060 --> 01:19:10,990
Going somewhere?

1282
01:19:12,320 --> 01:19:13,470
Besides jail?

1283
01:19:21,230 --> 01:19:22,880
No,not in the face,man. please.

1284
01:19:23,090 --> 01:19:24,530
If you know what's good for you,Tighten,

1285
01:19:24,740 --> 01:19:26,240
you'll stay out of Metrocity!

1286
01:19:26,460 --> 01:19:27,680
- You got it! - For good!

1287
01:20:03,260 --> 01:20:04,510
Pretty sneaky,sis.

1288
01:20:05,450 --> 01:20:06,480
But there's only one person

1289
01:20:06,680 --> 01:20:08,470
I know who calls this town "Metrocity."

1290
01:20:10,280 --> 01:20:11,050
You.

1291
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:16,100
Bet you think it's really funny?

1292
01:20:18,190 --> 01:20:19,970
Let's all laugh at the really cool guy?

1293
01:20:23,770 --> 01:20:25,350
Well,you're not gonna be laughing for long.

1294
01:20:26,530 --> 01:20:27,560
The invisible car.

1295
01:20:27,640 --> 01:20:29,780
Hey! Remember that night that I dumped you?

1296
01:20:31,550 --> 01:20:32,760
You're bringing this up now?

1297
01:20:33,300 --> 01:20:34,750
Well,I did look back!

1298
01:20:36,420 --> 01:20:38,750
You did? you did?

1299
01:20:39,100 --> 01:20:42,340
Yes! And you should look back right now!

1300
01:20:43,930 --> 01:20:45,110
Oh,I get it!

1301
01:20:53,430 --> 01:20:55,760
This is the last time you make a fool out of me!

1302
01:20:56,720 --> 01:20:58,030
I made you a hero.

1303
01:20:58,460 --> 01:21:02,110
You did the fool thing all by yourself.

1304
01:21:08,960 --> 01:21:10,310
You're so pathetic.

1305
01:21:10,690 --> 01:21:13,840
No matter what side you're on,you're always the loser.

1306
01:21:14,660 --> 01:21:15,990
There's a benefit to losing.

1307
01:21:16,830 --> 01:21:18,470
You get to learn from your mistakes.

1308
01:21:24,030 --> 01:21:25,750
Oh,you've got to be kidding me!

1309
01:21:26,110 --> 01:21:27,080
Minion,if I live,

1310
01:21:27,300 --> 01:21:28,170
I will kill you.

1311
01:21:39,120 --> 01:21:40,370
Enjoy your flight!

1312
01:21:42,780 --> 01:21:43,630
Megamind!

1313
01:21:51,640 --> 01:21:53,910
So this is how it ends.

1314
01:21:55,050 --> 01:21:58,470
Normally,I'd chalk this up to my last glorious failure.

1315
01:22:00,080 --> 01:22:01,430
But not today.

1316
01:22:02,460 --> 01:22:05,410
What can I say? Old habits die hard.

1317
01:22:12,580 --> 01:22:14,040
Say bye-bye,Roxie.

1318
01:22:29,480 --> 01:22:32,660
The thing about bad guys,they always lose!

1319
01:22:37,440 --> 01:22:39,510
You did it. You won.

1320
01:22:40,900 --> 01:22:44,680
I finally had a reason to win. You.

1321
01:22:53,970 --> 01:22:54,970
Minion!

1322
01:22:55,620 --> 01:22:59,470
Can't see. it's cold and... warm,and dark and light.

1323
01:22:59,680 --> 01:23:01,790
It's me,Minion. I'm right here.

1324
01:23:02,050 --> 01:23:04,960
We've had a lot of adventures together,you and I.

1325
01:23:05,230 --> 01:23:06,500
We have,Minion.

1326
01:23:09,160 --> 01:23:13,510
I mean... most of them ended in horrible failure,

1327
01:23:13,730 --> 01:23:17,920
But we won today. didn't we,sir?

1328
01:23:18,300 --> 01:23:20,320
Yes,Minion,we did it.

1329
01:23:20,680 --> 01:23:21,950
Thanks to you.

1330
01:23:22,190 --> 01:23:25,790
Code: We're the good guys now.

1331
01:23:26,250 --> 01:23:29,280
Code: I guess we are.

1332
01:23:30,530 --> 01:23:33,640
Oh,oh,oh,I'm going! I think this,this is it!

1333
01:23:33,830 --> 01:23:35,540
I'm going... going far...

1334
01:23:46,890 --> 01:23:48,430
What a drama queen.

1335
01:23:49,220 --> 01:23:52,580
You know,I'm feeling much better now. I guess I just needed a swim.

1336
01:23:52,820 --> 01:23:53,780
He had you,didn't he?

1337
01:23:54,610 --> 01:23:56,710
Classic Minion. Don't give me that face.

1338
01:23:57,170 --> 01:23:58,420
He reels you in with that little face.

1339
01:23:58,650 --> 01:24:00,400
- Look at that face. - We did it!

1340
01:24:00,970 --> 01:24:01,860
We did it!

1341
01:24:02,310 --> 01:24:03,850
- Fist pump! - You did it!

1342
01:24:04,160 --> 01:24:05,810
We won,we won,we won!

1343
01:24:08,420 --> 01:24:10,030
Get back,you savages!

1344
01:24:10,240 --> 01:24:14,060
Sorry! Sorry. He's just not used to positive feedback.

1345
01:24:17,670 --> 01:24:18,340
Funny,

1346
01:24:18,360 --> 01:24:21,090
I guess destiny is not the path given to us...

1347
01:24:24,450 --> 01:24:26,940
... but the path we choose for ourselves.

1348
01:24:35,130 --> 01:24:37,450
All right,put your hands in the air.

1349
01:24:41,110 --> 01:24:42,560
Now hand over your wallets.

1350
01:24:44,430 --> 01:24:45,350
I'm just kidding!

1351
01:24:46,640 --> 01:24:47,510
Just kidding!

1352
01:24:47,890 --> 01:24:51,910
I have to admit,being good has its perks.

1353
01:24:53,270 --> 01:24:55,720
You know,you look pretty good in white.

1354
01:24:56,110 --> 01:24:58,260
Megamind,if you plea...

1355
01:25:03,880 --> 01:25:05,480
Hey. My kid can't see.

1356
01:25:06,230 --> 01:25:07,370
Sorry,my friend.

1357
01:25:08,390 --> 01:25:11,670
Way to go,little buddy. I knew he had it in him.

1358
01:25:11,990 --> 01:25:13,500
Ladies and gentlemen,

1359
01:25:14,070 --> 01:25:17,920
Megamind,defender of Metro city!

1360
01:25:19,760 --> 01:25:22,910
You know,I like the sound of that.

1361
01:25:23,510 --> 01:25:24,290
Hit it!

1362
01:25:28,390 --> 01:25:37,440
Megamind! Megamind! Megamind! Megamind!

1363
01:25:43,970 --> 01:25:48,250
I'm bad! I'm bad! that's right. yeah!

1364
01:28:34,080 --> 01:28:37,250
Sir,you really need to empty your pockets more often.

1365
01:28:37,760 --> 01:28:40,550
This has been the worst day of my entire life.

1366
01:28:41,280 --> 01:28:42,460
No worries.

